#visit
  .container
    %section.visit
      .row
        .col-md-3.sidebar
          .roses
        .col-md-9.content
          %h1.section-title Visit Longsword
          %p.lead LongSword is a breathtaking Chardonnay and Pinot Noir vineyard located in the heart of the Applegate Valley.
          %p A pleasant 15 minute drive from downtown Jacksonville, LongSword features table-ready wines that are distinctly approachable, charming, and complex.
          %p.text-muted ----
          %h3 Here's a sampling of the lovely things Longsword has to offer!
          .row
            .col-md-3
              .global-patio
              %h4 Tasting Room and Patio
            .col-md-3
              .global-parasail
              %h4 Parasailing
            .col-md-3
              .global-boys
              %h4 The Vineyard and Menagerie
            .col-md-3
              .global-grapes
              %h4 Specialty Wines

    %section.tasting-room.sub-section
      .row
        .col-md-3.sidebar
        .col-md-9.content
          %h1.section-title Tasting room and patio
          %p.lead Enjoy chatting with locals in the coolness of the tasting room, or spend a relaxing afternoon in the shade on the sun-drenched patio.
          %p
            Both the tasting room and patio feature breath-taking views of the vineyard and the surrounding mountains. Tastings are complimentary and lingering is encouraged.
            %span.strong Open 12-5 daily.

    %section.vineyard.sub-section
      .row
        .col-md-12.content
          %h1.section-title Vineyard and Menagerie
          %p.lead Nestled between the Siskiyou, Cascade, and Coastal mountain ranges, LongSword encompasses 10 acres of Chardonnay and Pinot Noir vines and 12 acres of natural beauty.
          %p Thanks to the vineyard's unique microclimate, LongSword enjoys sunshine 360 days a year. Some stuff about the menagerie can go here.
    %section.parasailing.sub-section
      .row
        .col-md-3.sidebar
        .col-md-9.content
          %h1.section-title Parasailing
          %p.lead On any given afternoon, odds are you’ll see the colorful sails of hang gliders and parasailers growing large in the sky as they descend from Woodrat Mountain.
          %p Work your way through a bottle, and you'll probably even witness a daredevil landing or two in the field in front of the tasting room!
          %p.text-muted ----
          %h3 Interested in taking the plunge? Visit rvhpa.org to schedule a tandem flight and then land at LongSword for a glass of wine to celebrate your bravery.


